I see two problems:

 1. You open your FileWriter object with the name of the file instead of the file itself
 2. You do not close your FileWriter

This works for me:
```
  @Test
  public void getContentFile() throws IOException {
    File textFile = tempFolder.newFile(&quot;testText.txt&quot;);
    FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter(textFile);
    fileWriter.write(&quot;Line1 a&quot;);
    fileWriter.write(&quot;Line2 b c&quot;);
    fileWriter.write(&quot;Line3 3&quot;);
    fileWriter.close();
  }
```

You have to change textFile.*getName()* to textFile.*getPath()*, in the line where the **FileWriter** is created, as follows:

*From*

 - FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter(textFile.*getName()*);

*To* 
 - FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter(textFile.***getPath()***);

